WEBVTT

00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:35.400
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:00:35.765 --> 00:00:37.392
Are you out of your mind?

00:00:38.101 --> 00:00:39.811
Me? With that bastard?

00:00:41.646 --> 00:00:45.608
He's just an unlucky classmate
I got stuck with.

00:00:45.692 --> 00:00:47.235
I'd scrub him out if I could!

00:00:47.777 --> 00:00:50.864
For a classmate,
you sound extremely hostile.

00:00:50.947 --> 00:00:52.907
Whenever I think about that jerk,

00:00:52.991 --> 00:00:55.910
I jolt awake
in the middle of the night, fuming.

00:00:58.329 --> 00:01:00.832
Okay, I get it, so just drive carefully!

00:01:00.915 --> 00:01:02.208
You're a lawyer and yet…

00:01:02.292 --> 00:01:05.128
No, it's not me.

00:01:05.211 --> 00:01:08.673
-The car isn't listening to me.
-What?

00:01:12.427 --> 00:01:13.303
Se-na!

00:01:15.013 --> 00:01:16.973
Se-na!

00:01:17.056 --> 00:01:18.683
-Se-na!
-No, La-ik!

00:01:37.785 --> 00:01:39.495
Where's my Se-na?

00:01:42.874 --> 00:01:45.043
Where could my little girl be?

00:01:46.586 --> 00:01:47.545
There you are.

00:01:51.341 --> 00:01:53.760
Why is my Se-na so upset today?

00:01:55.595 --> 00:01:56.846
Se-na,

00:01:56.930 --> 00:01:58.806
your mom didn't scold you

00:01:58.890 --> 00:02:01.351
because you broke the pot.

00:02:01.434 --> 00:02:04.479
She scolded you
because you kept saying you didn't do it.

00:02:04.562 --> 00:02:06.189
I didn't do it.

00:02:06.814 --> 00:02:07.732
Really?

00:02:07.815 --> 00:02:09.859
So you didn't break it?

00:02:09.943 --> 00:02:11.653
Yeah! I didn't!

00:02:11.736 --> 00:02:14.113
I see.

00:02:16.574 --> 00:02:17.742
But that's strange.

00:02:18.326 --> 00:02:20.411
Why is this tree getting all ticklish?

00:02:22.497 --> 00:02:23.998
The tree?

00:02:24.749 --> 00:02:28.294
Se-na, this is a tickle tree.

00:02:28.378 --> 00:02:30.838
When someone tells a lie underneath it,

00:02:30.922 --> 00:02:32.465
its leaves start fluttering

00:02:32.548 --> 00:02:35.677
like it's getting tickled…

00:02:35.760 --> 00:02:37.637
-There!
-You're lying.

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:38.763
It's true.

00:02:39.555 --> 00:02:42.183
This tree has very thin bark,

00:02:42.267 --> 00:02:44.602
so what's outside and inside are the same.

00:02:44.686 --> 00:02:49.399
It always shows itself honestly.

00:02:50.024 --> 00:02:51.025
Just like you, Se-na.

00:02:54.779 --> 00:02:57.782
No, I…

00:03:00.785 --> 00:03:02.286
I…

00:03:16.175 --> 00:03:17.552
Dad?

00:03:19.637 --> 00:03:21.139
Dad.

00:03:26.811 --> 00:03:28.312
Dad?

00:04:21.115 --> 00:04:22.575
Dad.

00:04:32.126 --> 00:04:33.795
Dad!

00:04:36.547 --> 00:04:38.299
Dad!

00:04:39.801 --> 00:04:41.677
Dad!

00:04:47.141 --> 00:04:49.477
Dad.

00:05:04.367 --> 00:05:06.452
Attorney Maeng! Attorney Maeng?

00:05:19.340 --> 00:05:21.008
-Are you okay?
-Attorney Maeng?

00:05:24.804 --> 00:05:27.306
Are you okay? Were you hurt?

00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:30.977
The doctor said it's just an arm fracture.
No other injuries, thankfully.

00:05:31.060 --> 00:05:32.520
What exactly happened?

00:05:33.604 --> 00:05:36.399
Well, the car suddenly started acting up.

00:05:36.482 --> 00:05:38.109
-The car?
-Yes.

00:05:39.819 --> 00:05:41.988
Do La-ik, your head…

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:43.948
Why? Does it hurt?

00:05:44.031 --> 00:05:45.908
I'll go get the doctor.

00:05:47.577 --> 00:05:48.911
My arm…

00:05:50.496 --> 00:05:52.874
Ten years without an accident
and suddenly this?

00:05:52.957 --> 00:05:55.334
I don't know.
The steering just stopped responding.

00:05:55.418 --> 00:05:58.254
What about when you started the car?
Did the RPM spike out?

00:05:58.337 --> 00:06:00.006
I don't remember clearly.

00:06:01.549 --> 00:06:05.511
La-ik got out first,
and I stayed to talk to the prosecutor.

00:06:05.595 --> 00:06:07.013
I came down in a rush.

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:13.144
For now, find out which shop
is handling my car

00:06:13.227 --> 00:06:15.855
and figure out
what exactly caused the accident.

00:06:17.523 --> 00:06:18.691
Something

00:06:19.317 --> 00:06:20.484
doesn't feel right.

00:06:20.568 --> 00:06:22.862
Are you saying someone did it on purpose?

00:06:25.615 --> 00:06:28.492
Excuse me, our Attorney Maeng…
I mean, the patient just woke up.

00:06:28.576 --> 00:06:30.703
-Could you come quickly?
-What's the patient's name?

00:06:30.786 --> 00:06:32.788
It's Maeng Se-na.

00:06:34.957 --> 00:06:36.918
You have a car accident patient, right?

00:06:37.001 --> 00:06:38.669
He's a well-known figure…

00:06:38.753 --> 00:06:40.004
Is Mr. Do La-ik here?

00:06:40.087 --> 00:06:41.589
Could you please check it?

00:06:42.465 --> 00:06:43.716
-Excuse me.
-Did you see him?

00:06:46.469 --> 00:06:49.222
Se-na, we've got a problem.
Reporters are everywhere.

00:06:51.349 --> 00:06:52.266
Excuse me.

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:54.852
I think I'm okay now. Can I be discharged?

00:06:54.936 --> 00:06:55.937
Yes.

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:58.356
You're all done.
Just settle the bill and you can go.

00:06:59.357 --> 00:07:01.234
You're leaving?
You should rest a bit more.

00:07:01.317 --> 00:07:02.735
You're okay, right?

00:07:02.818 --> 00:07:04.070
Yes, I'm okay.

00:07:04.153 --> 00:07:05.571
-But--
-I'm fine too.

00:07:05.655 --> 00:07:07.573
It won't help if reporters see me now.

00:07:08.366 --> 00:07:10.868
Chung-jae, please take care of the rest.
Let's go.

00:07:26.467 --> 00:07:27.468
Taxi!

00:07:30.179 --> 00:07:31.305
La-ik, hurry up.

00:07:38.563 --> 00:07:39.480
There they are.

00:07:39.564 --> 00:07:41.107
-Isn't that him?
-The cab over there?

00:07:45.319 --> 00:07:46.153
Damn it.

00:07:46.237 --> 00:07:47.989
You still can't get that one done?

00:07:48.531 --> 00:07:51.367
How do you fail to lock up someone
who was caught at the scene?

00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:52.577
You said he was the one.

00:07:53.286 --> 00:07:56.581
The circumstantial evidence is solid.
We'll have the physical evidence soon.

00:07:57.957 --> 00:08:00.334
Imhwa Group is in an uproar.

00:08:00.418 --> 00:08:03.254
You tagged an innocent person
as an accomplice, not even a witness.

00:08:04.547 --> 00:08:06.340
Why drag their daughter?

00:08:07.049 --> 00:08:08.467
Can't you ever handle things quietly?

00:08:09.719 --> 00:08:11.971
-I apologize.
-Forget it.

00:08:12.054 --> 00:08:14.098
To take a case everyone wanted,

00:08:14.890 --> 00:08:16.684
you pulled strings,
got your father involved.

00:08:16.767 --> 00:08:19.020
So you'd better deliver.

00:08:19.103 --> 00:08:21.522
If you push on gut feeling
without evidence and it blows up,

00:08:21.606 --> 00:08:23.274
how are you going to handle the fallout?

00:08:23.774 --> 00:08:26.986
Bring me solid proof,
or admit your mistake

00:08:27.069 --> 00:08:28.988
and change course now.

00:08:46.422 --> 00:08:49.342
You said you wanted
to be a prosecutor, right?

00:08:50.176 --> 00:08:51.886
I hope that dream comes true,

00:08:51.969 --> 00:08:53.471
so you can watch me

00:08:53.554 --> 00:08:56.307
set everything straight
right in front of you.

00:09:03.397 --> 00:09:05.650
Man, look at that face.

00:09:06.525 --> 00:09:09.070
I heard the chief chewed you out.

00:09:09.737 --> 00:09:11.781
I guess you took a real beating.

00:09:11.864 --> 00:09:15.034
What is it? You have something?

00:09:15.117 --> 00:09:16.160
I do.

00:09:16.243 --> 00:09:19.330
I have fresh information.

00:09:20.414 --> 00:09:23.959
I checked Choi Jae-hee's alibi,
and the hospital confirmed

00:09:24.043 --> 00:09:26.212
Hong Hye-joo was right.

00:09:26.295 --> 00:09:29.298
So it's true Jae-hee
wasn't at the hospital?

00:09:30.091 --> 00:09:31.467
Yes.

00:09:31.550 --> 00:09:35.471
Something felt off,

00:09:35.554 --> 00:09:40.017
so I pulled all the CCTV around the lodge.

00:09:40.101 --> 00:09:41.352
And guess what,

00:09:41.435 --> 00:09:43.729
he shows up on it.

00:09:44.438 --> 00:09:48.984
I saw on the news that his group members
were at the hospital that night.

00:09:50.403 --> 00:09:51.487
That's not true.

00:09:51.570 --> 00:09:52.571
What?

00:09:52.655 --> 00:09:54.990
That night I saw him

00:09:56.659 --> 00:09:58.327
near La-ik's house.

00:09:59.662 --> 00:10:00.579
I saw Choi Jae-hee.

00:10:03.290 --> 00:10:07.253
Extend the scope.
Start an investigation on Choi Jae-hee.

00:10:07.336 --> 00:10:11.006
But if we shift to Jae-hee now,

00:10:11.799 --> 00:10:13.968
it'll clash with the Do La-ik case…

00:10:14.051 --> 00:10:16.679
We're not switching suspects.

00:10:16.762 --> 00:10:20.474
Choi Jae-hee or Do La-ik,
we tear them both apart the same way.

00:10:22.935 --> 00:10:25.980
Keep going until one of them confesses.

00:11:01.015 --> 00:11:03.768
Sir, could you please
drive a little slower?

00:11:03.851 --> 00:11:06.270
I am sorry.

00:11:35.633 --> 00:11:36.759
Thank you.

00:11:47.311 --> 00:11:49.855
Wait, did you hurt your foot? Let me see.

00:11:49.939 --> 00:11:52.316
No, it's just a cramp.

00:12:06.956 --> 00:12:08.415
What are you doing?

00:12:08.499 --> 00:12:11.126
Hold still.
You're making it heavier by squirming.

00:12:11.210 --> 00:12:13.837
You're gonna hurt your back!
You already have a herniated disc!

00:12:13.921 --> 00:12:15.548
How do you know I have a disc problem?

00:12:16.715 --> 00:12:19.885
A herniated disc
is a modern-day disease!

00:12:19.969 --> 00:12:22.054
Any adult can have it. I have it too!

00:12:23.639 --> 00:12:26.976
Seriously, couldn't you live
somewhere normal with an elevator?

00:12:27.059 --> 00:12:29.311
Put me down! Now!

00:12:29.395 --> 00:12:31.564
-Hold still.
-Seriously!

00:12:31.647 --> 00:12:32.898
Why…

00:12:33.399 --> 00:12:34.483
My God.

00:12:36.235 --> 00:12:37.736
-I'm dying.
-What's wrong with you?

00:12:39.113 --> 00:12:40.739
I told you to just put me down!

00:12:40.823 --> 00:12:42.408
You're hurt!

00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:45.202
I don't ignore someone who's hurt.

00:12:46.078 --> 00:12:48.539
Until you're healed,
I'll handle everything.

00:12:48.622 --> 00:12:50.332
So don't do anything, okay?

00:13:15.232 --> 00:13:16.900
I sincerely apologize.

00:13:17.568 --> 00:13:21.030
My son tends to charge ahead
recklessly during investigations.

00:13:21.614 --> 00:13:24.450
So I have to learn from a reporter

00:13:24.533 --> 00:13:27.536
that my daughter sat
in a prosecutor's office for six hours

00:13:27.620 --> 00:13:28.829
being questioned?

00:13:30.372 --> 00:13:32.916
Do you know how hard
I had to work to kill that story?

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:34.168
My apologies.

00:13:34.918 --> 00:13:36.879
If I had known she was your daughter,

00:13:37.546 --> 00:13:39.632
I would never have allowed
such disrespect.

00:13:39.715 --> 00:13:41.925
There's a difference
between being relentless

00:13:42.009 --> 00:13:43.636
and going against the flow.

00:13:43.719 --> 00:13:47.348
You said the culprit
is practically caught already.

00:13:47.431 --> 00:13:48.849
Yet why are you stumbling like this?

00:13:48.932 --> 00:13:50.225
Investigations

00:13:50.809 --> 00:13:54.188
must be led by evidence.

00:13:54.271 --> 00:13:56.523
We're still missing the decisive proof.

00:13:57.149 --> 00:14:00.152
Back in your day, you weren't like this.

00:14:00.819 --> 00:14:03.405
You handled things cleanly
without unnecessary noise.

00:14:05.824 --> 00:14:07.284
It seems your son falls

00:14:07.368 --> 00:14:10.287
far short of that decisiveness
and precision.

00:14:10.954 --> 00:14:13.666
He's still young and inexperienced.

00:14:13.749 --> 00:14:17.419
Please grant him
just a little more patience.

00:14:18.379 --> 00:14:21.715
Cases like this only get worse

00:14:21.799 --> 00:14:24.301
the longer they drag on.

00:14:24.843 --> 00:14:26.178
If needed,

00:14:26.261 --> 00:14:29.181
you should consider
shaping the flow yourself,

00:14:30.516 --> 00:14:32.601
just as you once did.

00:14:44.154 --> 00:14:46.073
He's already been discharged
from the hospital.

00:14:46.156 --> 00:14:47.533
Thankfully, it wasn't serious.

00:14:47.616 --> 00:14:50.786
And his whereabouts are still unknown?

00:14:51.537 --> 00:14:52.454
I'm sorry.

00:14:54.707 --> 00:14:56.458
Are you hiding something?

00:14:56.542 --> 00:14:57.960
No, ma'am.

00:14:58.669 --> 00:15:01.005
But if the Chairman finds out,
he'll be furious--

00:15:01.088 --> 00:15:03.507
I'll handle it myself, so please…

00:15:07.386 --> 00:15:09.763
find him as soon as you can.

00:15:10.556 --> 00:15:12.266
I need to know where he is.

00:15:16.603 --> 00:15:18.439
PEANUT BUTTER

00:15:20.733 --> 00:15:22.359
There's nothing to cook with.

00:15:40.461 --> 00:15:42.671
FRESH MILK

00:15:52.181 --> 00:15:55.142
Se-na, are you okay?

00:15:58.645 --> 00:15:59.605
Se-na?

00:16:05.694 --> 00:16:06.737
Why? What is it?

00:16:07.780 --> 00:16:09.323
I'm fine. Why?

00:16:09.406 --> 00:16:12.493
I heard something breaking in there.

00:16:25.089 --> 00:16:27.341
-Come here.
-Why?

00:16:28.175 --> 00:16:29.468
Why?

00:16:29.551 --> 00:16:31.011
I said I'm fine, why?

00:16:31.095 --> 00:16:32.763
Sit down. Just for a second.

00:16:32.846 --> 00:16:33.764
-I'm fine.
-Sit here.

00:16:33.847 --> 00:16:36.266
I can just dry it with a dryer.

00:16:36.767 --> 00:16:38.185
Okay?

00:16:38.268 --> 00:16:40.729
Why are you doing this?

00:16:43.899 --> 00:16:45.484
Use this and dry it.

00:16:58.789 --> 00:17:01.500
You hurt your hand too.
Skipping a shower once won't kill you.

00:17:01.583 --> 00:17:03.585
No way. I'll smell.

00:17:03.669 --> 00:17:05.546
You washed your hair this morning.

00:17:05.629 --> 00:17:07.131
That's enough, it won't smell.

00:17:08.632 --> 00:17:09.466
Stinky Se-na.

00:17:20.310 --> 00:17:21.979
-Stinky Se-na?
-What?

00:17:22.062 --> 00:17:25.149
Is that your childhood nickname?

00:17:25.774 --> 00:17:26.733
No, it's not.

00:17:26.817 --> 00:17:29.278
Come on. I heard him call you that.

00:17:32.072 --> 00:17:35.742
It was just because of my name.
It wasn't because I actually smell.

00:17:40.164 --> 00:17:41.540
I know it's not true,

00:17:42.457 --> 00:17:44.668
but when people keep calling me that,

00:17:44.751 --> 00:17:46.128
I can't help thinking

00:17:46.962 --> 00:17:48.380
maybe it is.

00:17:48.463 --> 00:17:50.090
What do you mean by "maybe it is"?

00:17:50.174 --> 00:17:52.676
He's ridiculous. His name means germ.

00:17:53.552 --> 00:17:55.846
His name is Germ,
and he's teasing your name?

00:17:55.929 --> 00:17:58.807
He's the weird one. Seriously.
Even his personality's weird.

00:18:52.069 --> 00:18:53.654
I'm hungry.

00:18:53.737 --> 00:18:55.614
Wait a minute.

00:19:36.280 --> 00:19:38.740
Seriously, I'm not invisible.

00:19:40.158 --> 00:19:43.578
Shouldn't you at least talk to the person
you're eating with?

00:19:47.916 --> 00:19:50.460
Sorry, I had something urgent
to look over.

00:19:51.962 --> 00:19:55.507
Anyway, you seem polite
and rude at the same time.

00:19:57.092 --> 00:19:59.636
Says the man who spoke informally
to me the moment we met.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:01.263
I don't talk like that to anyone.

00:20:02.264 --> 00:20:05.017
It just feels natural with you.
So it slips out.

00:20:06.310 --> 00:20:07.602
You could talk casually back.

00:20:11.231 --> 00:20:12.107
No.

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:16.153
That'd make us seem way too close.

00:20:16.737 --> 00:20:17.654
Really?

00:20:18.196 --> 00:20:20.615
Most people like it
when I drop formalities.

00:20:20.699 --> 00:20:22.117
Makes them feel closer to me.

00:20:22.200 --> 00:20:23.160
That's…

00:20:24.953 --> 00:20:27.289
what people who like you say.

00:20:27.372 --> 00:20:30.375
For someone saying that,
you seem to like me a lot.

00:20:31.835 --> 00:20:33.128
Did you know that?

00:20:33.211 --> 00:20:35.297
All of this, I was the one
who advertised them.

00:20:36.757 --> 00:20:38.383
Really?

00:20:38.467 --> 00:20:40.427
Yeah, really. Look.

00:20:41.261 --> 00:20:44.348
How did you manage to buy

00:20:44.431 --> 00:20:46.725
only the products I endorsed?
Isn't that amazing?

00:20:46.808 --> 00:20:49.728
Really? Let me see.

00:20:51.104 --> 00:20:52.689
You're right.

00:20:52.773 --> 00:20:55.317
This was you.

00:20:56.026 --> 00:20:57.444
That's funny.

00:21:00.030 --> 00:21:01.281
To me…

00:21:03.200 --> 00:21:05.285
this can't be a coincidence.

00:21:09.331 --> 00:21:12.000
You bought them
because they're the best-selling ones.

00:21:12.084 --> 00:21:13.794
Right. Yeah.

00:21:14.878 --> 00:21:18.173
They're the best ones. I like them.

00:21:18.882 --> 00:21:21.259
Nope. They all taste the same.

00:21:21.885 --> 00:21:26.640
What changes it is
whether my face is on it.

00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:31.395
But the funny thing is,
I can't even drink milk.

00:21:31.478 --> 00:21:32.562
I am lactose intolerant.

00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:34.606
Really?

00:21:34.689 --> 00:21:36.525
I had no idea.

00:21:37.234 --> 00:21:39.694
Of course you didn't. I'm a product.

00:21:39.778 --> 00:21:41.363
A product that must never be opened.

00:21:44.366 --> 00:21:47.285
People twist off my lid…

00:21:49.496 --> 00:21:51.832
lick a little…

00:21:56.711 --> 00:21:59.923
and if they ever find out
how terrible it actually tastes, I'm done.

00:22:06.721 --> 00:22:09.391
Why are you saying things like that?

00:22:10.684 --> 00:22:12.060
What do you mean?

00:22:12.144 --> 00:22:14.729
Why do you talk about yourself that way?

00:22:15.897 --> 00:22:18.859
You were loved by so many people.

00:22:19.776 --> 00:22:21.486
But you always acted

00:22:22.487 --> 00:22:25.157
like you despise the people who love you.

00:22:25.240 --> 00:22:26.950
That always felt strange to me.

00:22:29.286 --> 00:22:30.829
And now I'm thinking…

00:22:33.498 --> 00:22:35.876
maybe the one you really hate

00:22:36.501 --> 00:22:38.837
is yourself.

00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:41.923
Maybe that's why
you don't believe any of it,

00:22:42.007 --> 00:22:44.801
because you think
you don't deserve to be loved.

00:22:47.971 --> 00:22:49.347
Spoken like a lawyer.

00:22:50.056 --> 00:22:52.475
You're smart, insightful,

00:22:52.559 --> 00:22:55.395
but you got one thing wrong.

00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:00.233
I've never been loved.

00:23:01.526 --> 00:23:02.986
People love Do La-ik of Gold Boys.

00:23:03.987 --> 00:23:05.614
Not me.

00:23:06.740 --> 00:23:09.075
That Do La-ik, he deserves love.

00:23:10.577 --> 00:23:11.912
But I'm not.

00:23:11.995 --> 00:23:15.916
I don't know how to give it or receive it.

00:23:16.917 --> 00:23:18.877
All I do is complain.

00:23:21.713 --> 00:23:24.007
Only one person ever understood that…

00:23:25.967 --> 00:23:27.844
and now even that person's gone.

00:23:32.933 --> 00:23:34.267
Which is why I'm relieved.

00:23:35.477 --> 00:23:37.312
You don't like me at all.

00:23:39.272 --> 00:23:41.024
Since you don't,

00:23:42.108 --> 00:23:43.735
you'll never be disappointed in me.

00:23:44.361 --> 00:23:45.237
Right?

00:24:02.087 --> 00:24:03.713
The tire blew out.

00:24:03.797 --> 00:24:07.175
That's why the steering didn't work
and the brakes felt weak.

00:24:08.343 --> 00:24:10.470
The pressure sensor
didn't go off either, right?

00:24:11.304 --> 00:24:14.182
It burst because someone
tried to puncture it and didn't finish it.

00:24:15.183 --> 00:24:18.144
You mean
someone did this on purpose?

00:24:19.938 --> 00:24:21.356
See this hole?

00:24:21.439 --> 00:24:23.775
Looks like someone jabbed it
with something sharp.

00:24:23.858 --> 00:24:26.069
All of them need to be replaced.

00:24:26.152 --> 00:24:29.447
Unbelievable.
Who would do something like this?

00:24:37.539 --> 00:24:40.292
I knew something was off.

00:24:41.543 --> 00:24:43.503
So did you report it to the police?

00:24:44.045 --> 00:24:47.299
Yeah, but they're dragging their feet.
So I'm looking into it myself.

00:24:50.051 --> 00:24:52.637
And your dashcam was off for days.

00:24:53.805 --> 00:24:55.974
It's recording, right?

00:24:56.057 --> 00:24:58.893
The dashcam, I wish you'd turned it off.

00:25:02.147 --> 00:25:03.690
I turned it off for a bit.

00:25:04.482 --> 00:25:06.735
I must've forgotten to turn it back on.

00:25:33.136 --> 00:25:34.763
Why is he here again?

00:25:54.407 --> 00:25:56.993
What are they talking about this early?

00:25:57.660 --> 00:25:59.746
What are those two to each other?

00:26:02.123 --> 00:26:03.917
Why do I care?

00:26:04.501 --> 00:26:05.877
Whatever they are.

00:26:13.843 --> 00:26:16.513
I checked the CCTV at the parking lot
near your place too.

00:26:16.596 --> 00:26:17.931
Nothing suspicious.

00:26:18.473 --> 00:26:20.809
I'll check the cameras
near your office later.

00:26:21.768 --> 00:26:22.727
But…

00:26:23.520 --> 00:26:26.022
-Don't you think it's too coincidental?
-What do you mean?

00:26:26.106 --> 00:26:28.942
The accident happened that day…
Isn't that strange?

00:26:30.819 --> 00:26:33.530
You said La-ik came down first
that day, right?

00:26:39.702 --> 00:26:41.830
What if that moment was his chance?

00:26:56.636 --> 00:26:58.513
A chance to prove he was innocent.

00:27:03.184 --> 00:27:07.730
-And how would that prove anything?
-I'm just saying, look at the possibility.

00:27:08.231 --> 00:27:09.149
Think about it.

00:27:10.275 --> 00:27:12.902
Who would gain from something like that?
Only Do La-ik.

00:27:13.736 --> 00:27:15.155
If he had a non-fatal accident,

00:27:15.238 --> 00:27:17.740
he could claim
someone was trying to murder him,

00:27:18.741 --> 00:27:20.702
that he's not the real culprit.

00:27:20.785 --> 00:27:22.495
Then he walks away innocent.

00:27:24.080 --> 00:27:27.167
Chung-jae, quit the mystery novels.

00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:28.877
Quit the games.

00:27:28.960 --> 00:27:32.005
Say something that makes sense.
Who risks their own life like that?

00:27:32.088 --> 00:27:35.258
Someone who might rot in prison
for the rest of his life.

00:27:36.301 --> 00:27:38.470
If he killed someone, what wouldn't he do?

00:27:39.179 --> 00:27:40.388
Don't say that.

00:27:43.099 --> 00:27:46.519
Yes, he's rude, self-centered,

00:27:46.603 --> 00:27:49.022
and infuriating most of the time…

00:27:59.073 --> 00:28:02.660
but he would never do something like that.

00:28:04.120 --> 00:28:05.663
And how would you know?

00:28:07.540 --> 00:28:08.458
Chung-jae,

00:28:09.667 --> 00:28:11.294
don't you remember when we first met?

00:28:12.003 --> 00:28:15.381
You were arrested for pickpocketing twice,
and I defended you.

00:28:15.465 --> 00:28:17.550
I told you there wouldn't be
a third defense.

00:28:18.676 --> 00:28:19.594
I don't remember.

00:28:19.677 --> 00:28:21.262
Why are you bringing up old stuff?

00:28:21.346 --> 00:28:23.348
When you called me the third time,

00:28:24.307 --> 00:28:26.976
I really wasn't going to take your case.

00:28:27.060 --> 00:28:29.896
But you said

00:28:29.979 --> 00:28:32.148
you didn't do it.

00:28:32.232 --> 00:28:34.400
You begged me to believe you, just once.

00:28:36.528 --> 00:28:37.987
You know better than anyone

00:28:39.739 --> 00:28:41.825
how powerful it is

00:28:42.367 --> 00:28:44.702
when someone believes you.

00:28:46.955 --> 00:28:51.751
So I'm going to believe my client
until the end…

00:28:53.795 --> 00:28:55.171
at least for now.

00:29:04.264 --> 00:29:05.682
I didn't do it!

00:29:05.765 --> 00:29:07.934
How can you suspect me?

00:29:08.017 --> 00:29:12.105
I was hospitalized that day!
Do La-ik beat me up!

00:29:19.821 --> 00:29:20.822
Then what is this?

00:29:23.408 --> 00:29:25.159
We already confirmed on CCTV

00:29:25.243 --> 00:29:28.204
that you left the hospital
and went straight to the lodge.

00:29:29.539 --> 00:29:31.416
Why did you lie?

00:29:31.916 --> 00:29:33.209
I…

00:29:33.710 --> 00:29:35.128
-It's…
-Mr. Choi.

00:29:36.462 --> 00:29:42.176
Lying about your alibi
strongly suggests you're hiding something.

00:29:43.595 --> 00:29:45.930
Depending on how this goes,
you may no longer

00:29:46.014 --> 00:29:48.141
-be a witness, but a suspect.
-What?

00:29:48.224 --> 00:29:50.852
Why are you pinning this on wrong person?

00:29:50.935 --> 00:29:53.521
Mr. Choi, please, don't get agitated…

00:29:53.605 --> 00:29:55.982
How am I supposed to stay calm?
He's accusing me now!

00:29:56.065 --> 00:29:59.569
Why are you harassing an innocent person
when the real culprit is in front of you?

00:30:00.153 --> 00:30:03.615
I told you before! Do La-ik is the killer!

00:30:03.698 --> 00:30:05.867
There's no evidence that he's the culprit.

00:30:05.950 --> 00:30:08.870
-You need something concrete--
-I do! I have proof.

00:30:10.413 --> 00:30:13.833
Do La-ik had a reason
to kill Woo-seong.

00:30:19.714 --> 00:30:21.591
How much does the prosecution know?

00:30:22.300 --> 00:30:24.260
I'm not sure yet.

00:30:24.344 --> 00:30:28.890
I told his lawyer to keep Jae-hee
from saying anything for now, but…

00:30:28.973 --> 00:30:30.350
And how much does Jae-hee know?

00:30:32.310 --> 00:30:34.312
I said, how much does he know?

00:30:35.480 --> 00:30:37.440
I don't think he knows about Woo-seong.

00:30:45.907 --> 00:30:47.533
If it hurts, tell me.

00:31:01.047 --> 00:31:02.090
Okay.

00:31:03.007 --> 00:31:04.258
Try moving it.

00:31:10.807 --> 00:31:11.724
Are you okay?

00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:14.268
It's fine. Doesn't hurt at all.

00:31:14.352 --> 00:31:15.812
Good.

00:31:21.150 --> 00:31:24.237
Well, great.
I don't have to babysit you anymore.

00:31:25.113 --> 00:31:27.156
Good for me.

00:31:31.786 --> 00:31:32.912
Attorney Maeng.

00:31:39.168 --> 00:31:41.629
See? I told you it wasn't him.

00:31:41.713 --> 00:31:43.381
You need to quit those detective novels.

00:31:43.464 --> 00:31:45.591
I just said it might be possible!

00:31:46.551 --> 00:31:48.428
Wait, Se-na.

00:31:49.512 --> 00:31:51.014
I'm coming with you.

00:31:52.265 --> 00:31:53.599
Just stay home.

00:31:53.683 --> 00:31:55.935
-I'm going straight to the office anyway--
-Why?

00:31:56.978 --> 00:31:59.856
He should hear it too.
He should know who caused this to happen.

00:32:06.904 --> 00:32:08.281
Come on.

00:32:09.866 --> 00:32:11.743
Don't try to deny it.

00:32:11.826 --> 00:32:13.911
It's all on CCTV.

00:32:14.787 --> 00:32:15.663
Look.

00:32:17.081 --> 00:32:18.416
This is you two, right?

00:32:19.917 --> 00:32:21.377
Are you going to keep denying it?

00:32:27.800 --> 00:32:30.470
-These are the people?
-Yes.

00:32:32.346 --> 00:32:33.473
Damn it.

00:32:37.226 --> 00:32:38.144
Hey.

00:32:40.605 --> 00:32:43.232
-We have met before, right?
-You know each other?

00:32:44.484 --> 00:32:46.694
You can't abandon us!

00:32:47.278 --> 00:32:49.781
Not until we end you!

00:32:49.864 --> 00:32:51.574
You're not escaping!

00:32:51.657 --> 00:32:54.619
-You two…
-You do know each other.

00:32:56.287 --> 00:32:59.707
So that story about
just messing with some random car,

00:32:59.791 --> 00:33:01.292
that was a lie, right?

00:33:01.375 --> 00:33:02.376
We had a reason.

00:33:02.877 --> 00:33:05.713
-What?
-We did it because we had a reason!

00:33:07.048 --> 00:33:08.299
You're so brazen.

00:33:08.800 --> 00:33:10.760
How can you stand there
acting all innocent

00:33:10.843 --> 00:33:12.678
after killing our Woo-seong?

00:33:12.762 --> 00:33:16.641
A murderer is walking around free

00:33:16.724 --> 00:33:17.934
because of her!

00:33:19.102 --> 00:33:20.520
That's not right, is it?

00:33:20.603 --> 00:33:22.271
That's right.

00:33:22.897 --> 00:33:27.068
A lawyer defending scum like him
and threatening us.

00:33:27.819 --> 00:33:30.863
-She deserves whatever's coming.
-Hey!

00:33:32.073 --> 00:33:34.826
Someone almost died because of you two.

00:33:34.909 --> 00:33:37.620
Someone already died
because of him!

00:33:37.703 --> 00:33:38.913
Okay, okay.

00:33:38.996 --> 00:33:39.997
Everyone, calm down.

00:33:40.081 --> 00:33:43.668
You realize you just admitted
to intentionally damaging my car, right?

00:33:44.544 --> 00:33:47.839
Detective, this isn't just
property damage.

00:33:47.922 --> 00:33:51.384
Because of them,
we ended up in the hospital.

00:33:51.467 --> 00:33:53.845
This could be aggravated assault,
attempted murder…

00:33:53.928 --> 00:33:55.680
Can't we just let them go?

00:33:58.516 --> 00:33:59.934
Let them go? Are you kidding me?

00:34:00.017 --> 00:34:02.228
We can file for non-prosecution.

00:34:04.564 --> 00:34:05.565
Are you sure you want to?

00:34:07.567 --> 00:34:09.402
Just promise me one thing.

00:34:09.485 --> 00:34:12.738
You can do whatever you want to me…

00:34:17.243 --> 00:34:19.662
but don't ever do this to someone else.

00:34:20.621 --> 00:34:21.747
Got it?

00:34:31.632 --> 00:34:34.051
Are you really okay
with letting them go like that?

00:34:36.554 --> 00:34:37.889
Yes.

00:34:38.931 --> 00:34:40.349
I'm sorry.

00:34:41.809 --> 00:34:43.728
This always happens, doesn't it?

00:34:43.811 --> 00:34:47.648
Even when they broke into your house,
you didn't report them.

00:34:47.732 --> 00:34:49.984
So the police never even knew.

00:34:51.235 --> 00:34:53.487
If you keep avoiding things like this…

00:34:53.571 --> 00:34:55.031
And if I don't avoid it?

00:34:55.781 --> 00:34:56.866
What should I do?

00:34:58.451 --> 00:35:01.078
If I report them and let an investigation,

00:35:01.579 --> 00:35:03.956
they'll do more crazy things.

00:35:04.957 --> 00:35:08.544
They act out because they want attention,
and when they get it, they escalate.

00:35:10.171 --> 00:35:13.799
They'll make up stories, dump them online,

00:35:14.467 --> 00:35:15.927
and enjoy the mess they create.

00:35:16.010 --> 00:35:20.097
Ruining people is nothing to them.

00:35:22.308 --> 00:35:23.351
I just…

00:35:24.727 --> 00:35:26.687
I don't want you going through that.

00:35:41.786 --> 00:35:43.120
Yes, Ye-sol.

00:35:46.832 --> 00:35:47.750
What?

00:35:50.378 --> 00:35:51.295
Attorney Maeng.

00:35:54.674 --> 00:35:56.008
Where is Attorney Hwang?

00:36:00.930 --> 00:36:02.098
Stay here for a moment.

00:36:02.181 --> 00:36:04.308
Ye-sol, could you show him
to my room, please?

00:36:04.392 --> 00:36:05.309
Yes.

00:36:12.358 --> 00:36:14.610
The prosecution requested
a face-to-face interrogation?

00:36:15.945 --> 00:36:17.571
Sit down first.

00:36:17.655 --> 00:36:19.407
Come on, sit. Let's talk.

00:36:24.453 --> 00:36:25.705
You need to drop this case.

00:36:26.706 --> 00:36:29.125
I'm telling you this for your own good.

00:36:29.208 --> 00:36:31.210
So what do you mean by that?

00:36:34.672 --> 00:36:37.800
Because of something Choi Jae-hee
said during his witness interview,

00:36:38.718 --> 00:36:40.428
the prosecution started moving.

00:36:41.012 --> 00:36:43.472
I can't give you details,

00:36:43.556 --> 00:36:46.142
but by now you should have an idea.

00:36:48.519 --> 00:36:53.316
The ship you're on
is sinking, okay?

00:36:53.899 --> 00:36:57.361
And you know this well, right?

00:36:57.445 --> 00:37:00.614
In principle, our firm is legal counsel
for Goldie Entertainment.

00:37:00.698 --> 00:37:04.618
One law firm can't assist
two hostile clients in the same matter.

00:37:05.202 --> 00:37:07.121
That's a conflict of interest. Right?

00:37:07.204 --> 00:37:08.164
But--

00:37:08.247 --> 00:37:11.125
No need to argue.
The decision's already been made.

00:37:12.043 --> 00:37:14.628
And looking at how things are going,

00:37:14.712 --> 00:37:18.716
staying on this case will only hurt you.

00:37:19.550 --> 00:37:21.385
Public opinion isn't good either.

00:37:22.928 --> 00:37:24.722
So you're telling me

00:37:25.306 --> 00:37:26.807
to drop my client?

00:37:28.934 --> 00:37:32.188
Let's be honest, you're just trying
to get your name out there, right?

00:37:32.271 --> 00:37:33.856
But this case?

00:37:33.939 --> 00:37:35.399
Though it's a celebrity thing,

00:37:36.400 --> 00:37:38.152
there's no real money in it, right?

00:37:38.736 --> 00:37:40.112
Come on, Attorney Hwang.

00:37:43.324 --> 00:37:47.411
Handling this won't benefit you at all.

00:37:47.495 --> 00:37:49.413
We're saying this because we care.

00:37:50.956 --> 00:37:54.627
Remember that CEO assault case
at CheongyI Group?

00:37:54.710 --> 00:37:56.670
Looks like we might land it. Right?

00:37:56.754 --> 00:37:58.130
-Right.
-Yes.

00:37:58.214 --> 00:38:00.174
We'll give that one to you. How's that?

00:38:07.598 --> 00:38:09.683
"Even if the whole world turns its back,

00:38:10.643 --> 00:38:13.312
a lawyer must stand by their client.

00:38:13.396 --> 00:38:16.148
That's what a lawyer is."

00:38:17.858 --> 00:38:20.319
I became a lawyer
because of what you said.

00:38:23.239 --> 00:38:26.534
Because I wanted to be the one person

00:38:27.660 --> 00:38:30.121
who would hear out someone
no one else would believe.

00:38:37.920 --> 00:38:38.879
I understand

00:38:40.339 --> 00:38:41.799
what you are saying.

00:38:43.384 --> 00:38:44.427
But…

00:38:46.804 --> 00:38:48.848
I can't abandon this case.

00:38:50.182 --> 00:38:52.101
Until it's resolved,

00:38:52.184 --> 00:38:54.854
I'll stay away from everyone
at Cheon-un and stop coming in.

00:38:55.438 --> 00:38:57.565
If even that places a burden on the firm,

00:38:57.648 --> 00:39:01.318
I'll leave
the rest of the decision to you.

00:39:02.736 --> 00:39:04.071
Wait, Attorney Maeng…

00:39:04.155 --> 00:39:06.240
I'll be going now.

00:39:13.497 --> 00:39:16.167
Look at her,
playing hero of justice again.

00:39:17.209 --> 00:39:18.335
Don't you agree, sir?

00:39:30.264 --> 00:39:31.640
Why is there so much of it?

00:39:35.269 --> 00:39:36.395
Wait a second.

00:39:37.438 --> 00:39:38.606
Are you done?

00:39:46.071 --> 00:39:48.407
What is it? Did something happen?

00:39:49.742 --> 00:39:50.910
Choi Jae-hee

00:39:51.410 --> 00:39:54.163
had a witness interview
with the prosecution.

00:39:54.246 --> 00:39:56.457
And two of you
will have a face-to-face interrogation.

00:39:57.541 --> 00:40:00.002
What are you talking about?
A face-to-face?

00:40:00.085 --> 00:40:02.546
If they're preparing one,

00:40:02.630 --> 00:40:04.048
it likely means

00:40:04.131 --> 00:40:07.009
he gave a statement
that's unfavorable to you.

00:40:07.092 --> 00:40:09.470
The prosecution wants
to confirm it directly.

00:40:09.553 --> 00:40:12.389
Why would Jae-hee do that?

00:40:12.473 --> 00:40:15.434
Do you have any idea?

00:40:16.060 --> 00:40:18.437
Why he'd do that
or what he might've told them?

00:40:24.860 --> 00:40:29.198
We should prepare for every possibility,
and see if anyone around you

00:40:29.281 --> 00:40:32.076
might back up his statement.

00:40:32.159 --> 00:40:34.495
What if I meet Jae-hee myself?

00:40:34.578 --> 00:40:36.789
It's not illegal,

00:40:36.872 --> 00:40:38.707
but if we contact him
while the prosecution

00:40:38.791 --> 00:40:40.626
is preparing a confrontation,

00:40:40.709 --> 00:40:45.047
they could see it
as trying to influence his testimony.

00:40:45.839 --> 00:40:48.676
We need to be careful right now.

00:40:50.010 --> 00:40:51.136
But

00:40:52.263 --> 00:40:55.307
you can meet the person
who knows him best.

00:40:59.144 --> 00:41:00.771
I don't really know.

00:41:02.231 --> 00:41:04.942
When Jae-hee comes,
you can just ask him directly…

00:41:05.025 --> 00:41:06.443
No.

00:41:07.486 --> 00:41:09.738
We're here to talk to you, Young-bin.

00:41:12.324 --> 00:41:13.742
Young-bin,

00:41:14.285 --> 00:41:17.079
you know he was questioned
by the prosecution recently, right?

00:41:18.622 --> 00:41:22.835
Did Jae-hee tell you anything
about the interview?

00:41:23.377 --> 00:41:26.755
Or did anything seem off
before or after it?

00:41:26.839 --> 00:41:28.173
No, nothing at all.

00:41:30.384 --> 00:41:32.052
I really don't know anything.

00:41:32.761 --> 00:41:33.846
No.

00:41:34.680 --> 00:41:35.764
You do know.

00:41:36.682 --> 00:41:39.602
That night,
Jae-hee wasn't at the hospital,

00:41:40.686 --> 00:41:41.645
but you…

00:41:41.729 --> 00:41:43.314
Jae-hee was at the Hospital.

00:41:46.025 --> 00:41:47.943
You know that he was hospitalized with me.

00:41:48.027 --> 00:41:49.820
You said he was at the hospital.

00:41:51.572 --> 00:41:53.157
Why did you do that?

00:41:54.533 --> 00:41:55.618
Young-bin,

00:41:56.827 --> 00:41:59.038
you need to tell us the truth.

00:42:00.164 --> 00:42:03.792
For Kang Woo-seong
and for Choi Jae-hee.

00:42:03.876 --> 00:42:08.130
We can only get to the bottom of this
if you're honest.

00:42:15.804 --> 00:42:17.056
I'm sorry.

00:42:18.557 --> 00:42:20.768
He just told me to say that…

00:42:22.561 --> 00:42:26.315
Then, what exactly happened that night?

00:42:29.652 --> 00:42:31.320
That night…

00:42:40.829 --> 00:42:41.997
These jerks…

00:42:42.081 --> 00:42:43.916
NO ONE WOULD NOTICE IF JAE-HEE LEFT

00:42:43.999 --> 00:42:45.167
Come on.

00:42:45.250 --> 00:42:47.336
They're just talking. Don't mind it.

00:42:47.419 --> 00:42:48.545
Just talking?

00:42:49.171 --> 00:42:51.215
Does this look like just talking to you?

00:42:51.298 --> 00:42:54.468
It's not the first time.
La-ik's fans are just intense.

00:42:54.551 --> 00:42:56.845
He makes them like that.

00:42:58.013 --> 00:43:00.432
He's controlling them to bash me.

00:43:02.476 --> 00:43:03.477
Now what is this?

00:43:03.977 --> 00:43:07.231
Gold Boys member Do La-ik
held his first solo concert.

00:43:07.314 --> 00:43:10.401
The other members were supposed to guest,

00:43:10.484 --> 00:43:12.903
but their stage was canceled last minute.

00:43:12.986 --> 00:43:17.491
The label blamed sudden health issues,

00:43:18.075 --> 00:43:20.828
but insiders say Member B confronted A

00:43:20.911 --> 00:43:23.163
before the show and things escalated.

00:43:23.247 --> 00:43:24.873
What's the truth?

00:43:26.750 --> 00:43:28.419
Someone definitely leaked that.

00:43:32.673 --> 00:43:33.882
YOU ARE THE MEMBER B, RIGHT?

00:43:37.678 --> 00:43:40.013
This article's Member B,
that's you, right?

00:43:40.097 --> 00:43:42.433
Leave the group.

00:43:42.516 --> 00:43:45.352
Know your place.
You're nothing without La-ik.

00:43:51.650 --> 00:43:55.362
He seemed a bit upset
because of the comments,

00:43:55.446 --> 00:43:59.074
but it happens all the time,
so I didn't really think much of it.

00:43:59.825 --> 00:44:01.034
But then…

00:44:18.218 --> 00:44:20.387
I woke up for a moment,

00:44:20.471 --> 00:44:24.057
and Jae-hee was gone.

00:44:25.017 --> 00:44:26.935
He didn't answer his phone either.

00:44:28.562 --> 00:44:30.731
The nation is reeling

00:44:30.814 --> 00:44:33.108
after popular idol group member
Kang Woo-seong

00:44:33.192 --> 00:44:34.818
was found dead.

00:44:35.319 --> 00:44:38.781
What's most shocking is
that his body was discovered

00:44:38.864 --> 00:44:43.619
at the Seoul Gangseong-gu residence
of fellow group member Do La-ik.

00:44:43.702 --> 00:44:44.870
Police have confirmed

00:44:44.953 --> 00:44:47.456
that the two were together
on the day of the incident,

00:44:47.539 --> 00:44:48.874
and La-ik has been named the prime…

00:44:48.957 --> 00:44:53.253
-And then, I saw the news…
-He was taken into emergency custody…

00:44:53.337 --> 00:44:54.922
…that Woo-seong was gone.

00:44:59.176 --> 00:45:02.471
Then, did you ask Jae-hee?

00:45:02.554 --> 00:45:04.056
Where he actually went that day?

00:45:04.640 --> 00:45:05.891
I did.

00:45:06.892 --> 00:45:11.647
But he just told me to say we were
at the hospital together.

00:45:12.814 --> 00:45:14.316
And since CEO Geum

00:45:14.399 --> 00:45:18.529
already announced we were both there,
he said to stick to that story.

00:45:18.612 --> 00:45:20.614
Why didn't you tell me?

00:45:22.741 --> 00:45:24.701
You should have told me!

00:45:26.286 --> 00:45:27.579
It's…

00:45:48.559 --> 00:45:49.851
La-ik!

00:45:50.811 --> 00:45:53.522
Let's stop here for now.

00:45:55.148 --> 00:45:57.317
I'll contact you again later.

00:46:15.711 --> 00:46:16.753
Are you okay?

00:46:18.005 --> 00:46:18.964
What?

00:46:19.631 --> 00:46:21.925
Even if it was for Choi Jae-hee,

00:46:22.009 --> 00:46:23.594
a lie is still a lie.

00:46:24.886 --> 00:46:26.513
And because of that lie,

00:46:26.597 --> 00:46:29.474
you could be put in even more danger.

00:46:30.058 --> 00:46:32.102
He knew that, and still said nothing.

00:46:33.562 --> 00:46:35.230
I think I would've done the same.

00:46:38.942 --> 00:46:42.738
Jae-hee and Young-bin
have been close since they were trainees.

00:46:43.864 --> 00:46:45.699
Like brothers.

00:46:45.782 --> 00:46:47.618
How could he tell the truth?

00:46:48.660 --> 00:46:51.997
It would've felt like betraying Jae-hee.

00:46:53.165 --> 00:46:55.626
Then what about you?

00:46:58.754 --> 00:47:01.506
I heard you and Jae-hee didn't get along.

00:47:02.549 --> 00:47:05.552
Can I ask why?

00:47:09.806 --> 00:47:10.807
Because…

00:47:11.975 --> 00:47:13.769
I hurt him.

00:47:15.103 --> 00:47:16.271
A lot.

00:47:23.445 --> 00:47:24.613
What are you doing?

00:47:27.157 --> 00:47:28.575
What are you doing?

00:47:30.285 --> 00:47:31.286
Wow.

00:47:36.917 --> 00:47:37.876
So good.

00:47:39.294 --> 00:47:40.796
Why didn't you order seasoned one?

00:47:40.879 --> 00:47:44.508
We weren't like that from the beginning.

00:47:45.509 --> 00:47:46.760
But like always,

00:47:47.386 --> 00:47:49.471
trouble starts with something small.

00:47:59.022 --> 00:48:01.566
GOLD BOYS ON MUSIC LIVE ON
PROFESSIONALISM SHINES DESPITE HICCUP

00:48:04.194 --> 00:48:05.737
STILL LIVING OFF La-ik?
DRUMS FELL SHORT

00:48:05.821 --> 00:48:07.406
And by the time I realized it,

00:48:07.489 --> 00:48:09.366
it was already out of control.

00:48:22.879 --> 00:48:23.797
Okay.

00:48:32.013 --> 00:48:34.266
Jae-hee, if you're done resting,
let's run it once.

00:48:34.891 --> 00:48:38.437
What's the point? On music shows,
I use a fake stick and hand-sync anyway.

00:48:38.520 --> 00:48:40.188
Why bother rehearsing?

00:48:41.898 --> 00:48:43.483
Come on.

00:48:43.567 --> 00:48:45.152
Don't say that.

00:48:47.028 --> 00:48:48.029
Let's try it just once.

00:48:48.113 --> 00:48:50.282
Seriously, stop it!

00:48:53.201 --> 00:48:56.204
Hey, Choi Jae-hee,
what's with you lately?

00:48:56.288 --> 00:48:57.956
Skipping practice. Always on your phone.

00:48:58.832 --> 00:49:00.584
-Something wrong?
-Plenty.

00:49:01.585 --> 00:49:02.711
Because of you.

00:49:03.378 --> 00:49:07.215
You cut out my entire drum part,
said it didn't fit the song.

00:49:07.299 --> 00:49:09.926
Shouldn't you at least
feel bad about that?

00:49:10.802 --> 00:49:13.430
Jae-hee, we all agreed on that.

00:49:14.222 --> 00:49:16.641
The title track turned into a ballad.

00:49:16.725 --> 00:49:18.643
Your drum part
naturally had to get smaller.

00:49:18.727 --> 00:49:20.145
That's right.

00:49:20.228 --> 00:49:21.897
I get even fewer parts than you.

00:49:21.980 --> 00:49:25.734
Exactly! Why do we have to lose
all our parts and stand in the back?

00:49:25.817 --> 00:49:27.486
Then maybe get better from the start.

00:49:30.363 --> 00:49:33.116
I didn't take anything from you.
You lost it. Because you couldn't keep up.

00:49:35.619 --> 00:49:37.704
-Are you done?
-No, there's more.

00:49:38.330 --> 00:49:39.664
Everyone knows you go around

00:49:39.748 --> 00:49:43.043
saying you want to quit this stuff,
you don't need this to make a living.

00:49:43.126 --> 00:49:44.836
If that's how you think, then quit.

00:49:44.920 --> 00:49:47.255
We won't lose anything without you.

00:49:48.131 --> 00:49:49.424
And you know that.

00:49:49.508 --> 00:49:51.259
You know exactly where you stand here.

00:50:07.275 --> 00:50:08.193
You went too far.

00:50:10.403 --> 00:50:12.656
You didn't need to say it like that.

00:50:16.827 --> 00:50:17.702
Back then,

00:50:19.287 --> 00:50:21.540
I was young and immature.

00:50:25.043 --> 00:50:29.756
I treated people badly
and threw hurtful words around.

00:50:32.384 --> 00:50:34.928
I thought that was
the only way to succeed.

00:50:38.598 --> 00:50:40.433
I kept thinking…

00:50:42.352 --> 00:50:46.481
if someone really held
a grudge against me,

00:50:47.607 --> 00:50:48.525
who would it be?

00:50:56.157 --> 00:50:57.450
Turns out the list is long.

00:51:04.749 --> 00:51:08.503
So how can you believe someone like me?

00:51:11.923 --> 00:51:13.466
Can you really trust me?

00:51:17.053 --> 00:51:19.681
-What if I really did--
-I trust you.

00:51:23.268 --> 00:51:24.311
I trust

00:51:25.312 --> 00:51:27.272
myself who believes in you.

00:51:32.736 --> 00:51:34.988
Wait here. I have something to show you.

00:51:46.666 --> 00:51:47.751
Watch carefully.

00:51:52.172 --> 00:51:53.131
I believe

00:51:53.882 --> 00:51:55.592
in Do La-ik.

00:52:09.773 --> 00:52:12.817
I do not believe in Do La-ik.

00:52:23.578 --> 00:52:24.496
See that?

00:52:25.622 --> 00:52:28.875
This is a tickle tree.

00:52:29.793 --> 00:52:30.961
If someone lies,

00:52:31.044 --> 00:52:32.712
the leaves shake like this.

00:52:32.796 --> 00:52:35.840
Come on, that's impossible.

00:52:35.924 --> 00:52:38.051
Possible or not, it doesn't matter.

00:52:39.010 --> 00:52:40.136
I believe it.

00:52:42.931 --> 00:52:45.725
When this tree grows,

00:52:46.351 --> 00:52:48.269
it sheds its bark like this.

00:52:49.771 --> 00:52:51.481
When I was little, it looked painful,

00:52:52.399 --> 00:52:54.401
so I used to glue the bark back on,

00:52:55.110 --> 00:52:56.987
wrap it with bandages.

00:52:57.988 --> 00:53:00.198
But one day, my parents told me…

00:53:02.742 --> 00:53:05.078
a tree needs to shed its bark to grow.

00:53:05.161 --> 00:53:06.746
THE LATE MAENG JIYONG
THE LATE PARK SUHEE

00:53:19.092 --> 00:53:20.093
It's just…

00:53:22.137 --> 00:53:23.805
part of the process.

00:53:32.105 --> 00:53:34.399
But one day,

00:53:35.525 --> 00:53:37.652
after shedding all its bark,

00:53:38.445 --> 00:53:40.613
the tree showed its pale inner layer,

00:53:42.449 --> 00:53:43.533
and then…

00:53:45.702 --> 00:53:47.412
it started to bloom.

00:53:53.752 --> 00:53:55.754
But we're the opposite.

00:53:57.255 --> 00:54:00.133
As we grow, we build thicker bark

00:54:01.259 --> 00:54:02.802
and hide ourselves inside it.

00:54:06.556 --> 00:54:08.349
So we won't get hurt.

00:54:12.062 --> 00:54:13.104
So,

00:54:14.314 --> 00:54:18.109
when I look at this tree,
standing here completely exposed,

00:54:19.819 --> 00:54:21.613
I feel like

00:54:22.447 --> 00:54:24.199
I can trust what it tells me.

00:54:26.493 --> 00:54:27.577
I'm not brave enough yet

00:54:29.037 --> 00:54:31.623
to peel off all my bark either.

00:54:34.667 --> 00:54:37.378
Maybe that's why
I keep asking this tree…

00:54:39.672 --> 00:54:41.341
what I really want,

00:54:43.093 --> 00:54:44.886
whether I can trust myself,

00:54:45.804 --> 00:54:50.725
whether I'll ever be able to bloom too.

00:54:58.358 --> 00:55:02.862
When you don't know what to do,
I'll let you ask this tree too.

00:55:03.488 --> 00:55:08.409
If you hide everything inside,
you won't even know what you really want.

00:55:21.840 --> 00:55:22.715
I am

00:55:24.300 --> 00:55:25.635
handsome.

00:55:31.432 --> 00:55:33.434
I am a genius.

00:55:51.703 --> 00:55:52.620
I didn't

00:55:54.247 --> 00:55:55.331
harm…

00:55:57.709 --> 00:55:59.127
Woo-seong.

00:56:42.503 --> 00:56:44.005
Ms. Hong Hye-joo…

00:56:48.676 --> 00:56:49.802
You…

00:57:15.495 --> 00:57:16.913
It's…

00:57:17.830 --> 00:57:19.374
How could you do this as a lawyer?

00:57:35.431 --> 00:57:36.683
Let's go.

00:57:52.699 --> 00:57:53.616
No.

00:57:55.577 --> 00:57:56.869
You should leave.

00:57:58.871 --> 00:58:00.039
This is…

00:58:12.010 --> 00:58:13.511
where I belong.

00:59:18.159 --> 00:59:21.829
For La-ik, I've always been his only love.

00:59:21.913 --> 00:59:22.997
And it is the same for me.

00:59:23.081 --> 00:59:26.959
I don't know why,
but I fall apart around you.

00:59:27.043 --> 00:59:28.920
Right now,

00:59:29.754 --> 00:59:30.922
this is all I can give.

00:59:31.005 --> 00:59:33.049
If La-ik is really not the culprit…

00:59:33.132 --> 00:59:35.259
Now they suspect me.

00:59:35.760 --> 00:59:39.138
What if you found out
that someone you really trusted

00:59:39.222 --> 00:59:41.432
told you a huge lie?

00:59:41.516 --> 00:59:43.017
Explain it.

00:59:44.602 --> 00:59:49.607
Subtitle translation by: Alisha